alert.note: Alert for Interstate 5 Corridor; Western San Gabriel Mountains and Highway 14 Corridor (California) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: High Wind Warning issued December 08 at 7:12PM PST until December 09 at 3:00PM PST by NWS Oxnard
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 3 PM PST SATURDAY... * WHAT...Northeast winds 35 to 45 mph with damaging gusts up to 70 mph. * WHERE...Interstate 5 Corridor and Western San Gabriel Mountains and Highway 14 Corridor. * WHEN...For the High Wind Warning, from 7 PM this evening to 3 PM PST Saturday. * IMPACTS...Damaging winds will blow down large objects such as trees and power lines. Power outages are expected. Travel will be difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.
info.instruction: People should avoid being outside in forested areas and around trees and branches. If possible, remain in the lower levels of your home during the windstorm, and avoid windows. Use caution if you must drive.
